  "read": "TileLang row-blocked selected-K-chunk sparse-MLA backward dKV producer. It uses the same real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV inputs and the same chunk-level active-group metadata as recompute_pdp_chunked_grouped_dkv_limited, but each CTA owns only --row-block active compressed groups. This is the compile-safe fallback for S4096 when the full chunk-local active table is too large or too irregular for TileLang layout inference; it trades extra P/dP recompute for a static small reducer. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer.",
